184757"},{"from":{"fname":"zettel.20260421184845","id":"zettel.20260421184845","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":3,"offset":1082},"end":{"line":29,"column":28,"offset":1107},"indent":[]},"value":"zettel.20260421184757"},{"from":{"fname":"zettel.20260421184856","id":"zettel.20260421184856","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":27,"column":3,"offset":873},"end":{"line":27,"column":28,"offset":898},"indent":[]},"value":"zettel.20260421184757"},{"from":{"fname":"zettel.20260421184907","id":"zettel.20260421184907","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":27,"column":3,"offset":902},"end":{"line":27,"column":28,"offset":927},"indent":[]},"value":"zettel.20260421184757"},{"from":{"fname":"zettel.20260421185424","id":"zettel.20260421185424","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":3,"offset":2025},"end":{"line":50,"column":28,"offset":2050},"indent":[]},"value":"zettel.20260421184757"},{"from":{"fname":"zettel.20260421191335","id":"zettel.20260421191335","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":3,"offset":2878},"end":{"line":60,"column":28,"offset":2903},"indent":[]},"value":"zettel.20260421184757"},{"from":{"fname":"zettel.literature.bmad-advanced-elicitation","id":"zettel.literature.bmad-advanced-elicitation","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":48,"column":3,"offset":1779},"end":{"line":48,"column":28,"offset":1804},"indent":[]},"value":"zettel.20260421184757"},{"from":{"fname":"zettel.moc.ai-native","id":"zettel.moc.ai-native","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":57,"column":3,"offset":4986},"end":{"line":57,"column":28,"offset":5011},"indent":[]},"value":"zettel.20260421184757"}],"anchors":{"pertanyaan-yang-dibuka":{"type":"header","text":"Pertanyaan yang dibuka","value":"pertanyaan-yang-dibuka","line":17,"column":0,"depth":2},"klaim-utama":{"type":"header","text":"Klaim utama","value":"klaim-utama","line":23,"column":0,"depth":2},"penjelasan":{"type":"header","text":"Penjelasan","value":"penjelasan","line":29,"column":0,"depth":2},"built-in-methods":{"type":"header","text":"Built-in Methods","value":"built-in-methods","line":48,"column":0,"depth":2},"implikasi":{"type":"header","text":"Implikasi","value":"implikasi","line":60,"column":0,"depth":2},"lihat-juga":{"type":"header","text":"Lihat juga","value":"lihat-juga","line":67,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"zettel","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"advanced-elicitation-memaksa-model-menggunakan-lensa-berpikir-eksplisit-untuk-reconsider-output\">Advanced Elicitation memaksa model menggunakan lensa berpikir eksplisit untuk reconsider output<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#advanced-elicitation-memaksa-model-menggunakan-lensa-berpikir-eksplisit-untuk-reconsider-output\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"pertanyaan-yang-dibuka\">Pertanyaan yang dibuka<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#pertanyaan-yang-dibuka\"></a></h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Mengapa \"try again\" sering tidak cukup untuk output AI yang terlihat cukup baik?</li>\n<li>Bagaimana memilih lensa berpikir tertentu mengubah kualitas reconsideration model?</li>\n<li>Apa perbedaan antara kritik reviewer dan metode rencana ulang model?</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"klaim-utama\">Klaim utama<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#klaim-utama\"></a></h2>\n<p>Advanced Elicitation bukan sekadar second pass. Ini adalah second pass dengan epistemic lens yang dipilih untuk memaksa model memikirkan ulang outputnya secara terstruktur.</p>\n<p>Alih-alih meminta model \"improve this\" secara kabur, BMAD memaksa model menjalankan metode berpikir tertentu seperti pre-mortem, first principles, inversion, stakeholder mapping, atau socratic questioning.</p>\n<h2 id=\"penjelasan\">Penjelasan<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#penjelasan\"></a></h2>\n<p>Dalam BMAD, proses Advanced Elicitation terdiri dari tiga komponen:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>model menghasilkan output awal,</li>\n<li>manusia memilih metode berpikir yang relevan,</li>\n<li>model menerapkan metode itu pada outputnya sendiri,</li>\n<li>manusia lalu memutuskan apakah hasil kedua lebih baik.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Jenis metode yang disebutkan termasuk:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>pre-mortem analysis untuk melihat kegagalan potensial,</li>\n<li>first principles thinking untuk menggali asumsi dasar,</li>\n<li>inversion untuk mencari jalur gagalnya,</li>\n<li>red team vs blue team untuk menyerang dan membela argumen,</li>\n<li>socratic questioning untuk menantang klaim,</li>\n<li>stakeholder mapping untuk melihat berbagai perspektif,</li>\n<li>constraint removal untuk melepas asumsi arbitrer.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"built-in-methods\">Built-in Methods<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#built-in-methods\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184801\">Pre-mortem analysis memaksa perencanaan menilai hasil dengan asumsi kegagalan</a> — Pre-mortem analysis: asumsi gagal dulu supaya risiko tersembunyi muncul.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184812\">First principles thinking menuntut solusi dibangun dari fakta paling dasar</a> — First principles thinking: uji asumsi dasar dan hindari solusi templated.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184823\">Inversion mencari jalur gagal untuk menguji validitas desain</a> — Inversion: temukan jalur gagal untuk memperjelas risiko.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184834\">Red team vs blue team menguji ketahanan argumen lewat serangan dan pembelaan</a> — Red team vs blue team: serang dan bela argumen untuk menguji ketahanan.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184845\">Socratic questioning mengungkap asumsi lewat pertanyaan terarah</a> — Socratic questioning: tantang klaim dan buat bukti asumsi eksplisit.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184856\">Stakeholder mapping membuka risiko lewat banyak perspektif</a> — Stakeholder mapping: nilai artefak dari banyak perspektif.</li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184907\">Constraint removal mengecek apakah batasan itu nyata atau sekadar asumsi</a> — Constraint removal: cek apakah batasan itu nyata atau sekadar asumsi.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Setiap metode adalah lensa berpikir tersendiri; pilih yang paling pas untuk objek yang sedang direconsider.</p>\n<h2 id=\"implikasi\">Implikasi<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#implikasi\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Advanced Elicitation paling berguna ketika output awal terlihat masuk akal tetapi masih dapat menipu.</li>\n<li>Ini berguna untuk artefak high-stakes: spec, plan, architecture, dan draft review.</li>\n<li>Metode yang dipilih harus cocok dengan jenis artefak; tidak ada satu cara yang benar untuk semua.</li>\n<li>Hasil rerun tetap harus dievaluasi manusia; pass kedua adalah alternatif, bukan kebenaran otomatis.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"lihat-juga\">Lihat juga<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#lihat-juga\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184439\">Adversarial Review memaksa reviewer beralih dari rasa aman ke pencarian kelemahan</a> — Adversarial Review memaksa reviewer beralih dari rasa aman ke pencarian kelemahan</li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.literature.bmad-adversarial-review\">BMAD Adversarial Review sebagai literature note</a> — literature note BMAD Adversarial Review</li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.literature.bmad-quick-dev\">BMAD Quick Dev sebagai literature note</a> — literature note BMAD Quick Dev</li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.moc.ai-native\">MOC AI-native engineering</a> — MOC AI-native engineering</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"tags\">Tags<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#tags\"></a></h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">bmad (Private)</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">advanced-elicitation (Private)</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">ai-native (Private)</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">reasoning (Private)</a></li>\n</ol>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184801\">Pre-mortem analysis memaksa perencanaan menilai hasil dengan asumsi kegagalan</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184812\">First principles thinking menuntut solusi dibangun dari fakta paling dasar</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184823\">Inversion mencari jalur gagal untuk menguji validitas desain</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184834\">Red team vs blue team menguji ketahanan argumen lewat serangan dan pembelaan</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184845\">Socratic questioning mengungkap asumsi lewat pertanyaan terarah</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184856\">Stakeholder mapping membuka risiko lewat banyak perspektif</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421184907\">Constraint removal mengecek apakah batasan itu nyata atau sekadar asumsi</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421185424\">Party Mode adalah mesin konflik terkontrol untuk menampilkan trade-off multi-agent</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.20260421191335\">Pre-mortem bisa dilakukan tanpa event nyata dengan asumsi terstruktur, bukan nebak-nebak acak</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.literature.bmad-advanced-elicitation\">BMAD Advanced Elicitation sebagai literature note</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/sotoy/notes/zettel.moc.ai-native\">MOC AI-native engineering</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"root","title":"Hello and Welcome! 👋","desc":"","updated":1742030256619,"created":1646842475821,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"453f88f4a5f1ad7629ebb7cc49502125","links":[],"anchors":{"find-more":{"type":"header","text":"Find More","value":"find-more","line":20,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["book-summaries","daily","handbook","notes","tags","til","zettel"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\nWelcome to the homepage! I use Dendron to store and organize notes, ideas, and experiments I’m working on. Here are the main sections you’ll find on this site:\n\n1. **Learning Notes** — Practical notes on programming, recent technologies, and productivity tips.\n2. **Personal Projects** — Summaries of projects, experiments, and outcomes I’m working on or have completed.\n3. **Writings & Opinions** — Casual articles and reflections about technology, daily life, and other interesting topics.\n\nI’m constantly experimenting and learning. I hope the content here helps you as a reference, a starting point for discussion, or just light reading.\n\n> Why Dendron?\n>\nDendron helps keep notes organized. Its \"seed\" and \"vault\" concepts make it easy to structure content and find what you need.\n\n## Find More\n\nIf you want to learn more or connect, check these links:\n\n- [Homepage (Dendron)](https://zeihanaulia.github.io/sotoy/)\n- [My GitHub](https://github.com/zeihanaulia)\n- [My Twitter / X](https://x.com/zeihanaulia)\n\nThanks for stopping by. If you have feedback or want to chat, feel free to reach out.\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":true,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"smart","leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshol